# -- Triggers --
# Camera Target Corner
placements.triggers.HonlyHelper/CameraTargetCornerTrigger.tooltips.lerpStrength=Determines how fast the camera moves to lock into place upon activation.
placements.triggers.HonlyHelper/CameraTargetCornerTrigger.tooltips.positionMode=What corner this trigger occupies.
placements.triggers.HonlyHelper/CameraTargetCornerTrigger.tooltips.xOnly=The camera will only lock on the X axis.
placements.triggers.HonlyHelper/CameraTargetCornerTrigger.tooltips.yOnly=The camera will only lock on the Y axis.
placements.triggers.HonlyHelper/CameraTargetCornerTrigger.tooltips.deleteFlag=Session flag to deactivate the trigger, ignored if left empty. Camera will not reset if player is inside the trigger as it deactivates.\nIf the player transitions into the room with the flag set, the trigger can not be reactivated. However, if it was enabled and then disabled in the room, the player can reactivate it.


# Camera Target Crossfade
placements.triggers.HonlyHelper/CameraTargetCrossfadeTrigger.tooltips.lerpStrengthA=The lerp strength of Target Trigger A
placements.triggers.HonlyHelper/CameraTargetCrossfadeTrigger.tooltips.lerpStrengthB=The lerp strength of Target Trigger B
placements.triggers.HonlyHelper/CameraTargetCrossfadeTrigger.tooltips.positionMode=How the player goes from Target Trigger A to Trigger B.
placements.triggers.HonlyHelper/CameraTargetCrossfadeTrigger.tooltips.xOnly=The camera will only lock on the X axis.
placements.triggers.HonlyHelper/CameraTargetCrossfadeTrigger.tooltips.yOnly=The camera will only lock on the Y axis.
